      { question: 'Which fabrication skills are most in demand?', answer: 'CNC laser and plasma cutting operators are in high demand due to automation adoption. Press brake operators who can program modern CNC brakes are sought after. Layout and fit-up specialists who can work from drawings without detailed instructions are especially valued. Fabricators with structural steel experience benefit from infrastructure spending growth.' },
      { question: 'How do I advance from fabrication to management?', answer: 'Develop your blueprint reading and estimating skills to take on shop foreman responsibilities. Learn fabrication software (nesting, ERP, scheduling) to manage production workflows. Pursue AWS Certified Welding Inspector (CWI) credentials for quality oversight roles. Many fabrication shop managers started on the shop floor and advanced through demonstrated leadership and technical breadth.' }
