      { question: 'Is rigging experience from one industry transferable to others?', answer: 'Yes, rigging principles and certifications transfer across industries. NCCCO certification is recognized in construction, petrochemical, power generation, manufacturing, and offshore operations. The physics of load calculation and sling selection are universal. However, each industry has specific procedures and hazards, so expect some orientation when transitioning between sectors.' }
