      { question: 'Do I need to own my own hand tools for construction jobs?', answer: 'In most trades, yes. Employers typically expect workers to provide their own hand tools while supplying power tools and specialty equipment. Some unions specify minimum tool list requirements. Mention your tool ownership on your resume, as it demonstrates professionalism, investment in your career, and readiness to start work immediately.' },
      { question: 'How do precision hand tools differ from standard construction hand tools?', answer: 'Precision hand tools (micrometers, calipers, dial indicators, gauge blocks) measure to thousandths or ten-thousandths of an inch and are used in machining, quality control, and manufacturing. Standard construction hand tools (tape measures, levels, squares) measure to fractions of an inch. If you are applying for manufacturing or QC roles, emphasize precision instruments over construction tools.' }
